Request for Guidance, Documentation, and Working Session for BAMOE Usage on OpenShift
Description:
Hi IBM Support Team,

We are currently setting up IBM BAMOE (Business Automation Manager Open Editions) on OpenShift.

We have successfully followed the available IBM documentation and:

Deployed the BAMOE instance on OpenShift
Created and exposed the required routes
Accessed the BAMOE UI components successfully
Current Challenge:
While the deployment and access are working as expected, our team is new to BAMOE, and we are facing challenges in understanding how to proceed with actual usage.

Specifically, we need help with:

Creating and managing business applications (e.g., patient-related use cases)
Understanding how to design and use data models / tables (e.g., patient tables)
End-to-end workflow of developing and deploying applications within BAMOE
Best practices for using BAMOE in OpenShift environments
Request:
We kindly request:

Detailed documentation or learning resources
Step-by-step guides for beginners
Any official tutorials or sample use cases
Videos or training materials for BAMOE usage
Guidance on specific use case implementation
Example: Creating and managing “patient” data tables and workflows
A working session with IBM experts
A short session to walk us through:
Application creation
Data modeling
Deployment flow
This will help us align correctly and avoid implementation issues
Environment Details:
Platform: OpenShift
BAMOE Deployment: Operator / YAML-based (update as applicable)
Access: UI and routes are successfully working
Documentation followed: IBM official BAMOE setup guide
Expectation:
We are looking for guided support to move from setup → actual usage, including real-world examples and best practices.

✅ Optional (Add if needed)
